This is the same Mudrunner game available on PC and console, just with reduced graphics and worse controls due to the touchscreen. Multiplayer is also missing, which depending on how you play the game could drop the score much more. Overall 4/5 for me due to no mod support.

Peaceful yet challenging offroad truck game. If you played this on PC or console then you'll be happy to know it's a great port. If you never tried it then I highly recommend it. Check vids on YouTube at least first. Decent amount of content and it's infinitely replayable. If you like trucks and muddy roads then you'll be in heaven. Also check Snowrunner on PC or Consoles......it's awesome!

Good job. Expect to see Snow runner on Android too in future. The best thing if anyone asks me about this game is its not time bound and can really drive around as I want. For as long I want. The concept of the game is like an improvised version of the way I used to play with my toy trucks in mud in my childhood. I used to create my own tracks in the garden digging up all mud and adding hand made clay bridges reinforced by twigs dried in Sun. All those memories comes to life when I play.👍

A 1 to 1 port of the original game content. Graphics, controls and UI are good enough for a mobile port (silly to expect otherwise). Mud physics seemed toned down. Areas I dreaded crossing through on console seem to be a breeze in this. Regardless, if you want Mudrunner on the go, this is for you.

content: Amazing port of MudRunner to mobile. The game itself is great, but I a few requests. Firstly, an option to change the controls. The controls are good, but it would be great to have a gyro and a steering wheel option. Secondly, an option to change the graphics. My device isn't ultra-high-end, but it is Decent. I would like to change the graphics to my liking instead of the game configuring it for me. That's it. My experience has been good so far.
